            <title>[HBASE-13287] Append is missing methods, such as addColumn()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-13287</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Analog to Put, Delete, Get, etc. Append should have the same common method signature, namely &lt;tt&gt;addColumn()&lt;/tt&gt; as opposed to the older &lt;tt&gt;add()&lt;/tt&gt;. Also consider adding the other variant that Put has, including the &lt;em&gt;immutable&lt;/em&gt; versions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Question related: should those methods not better be in the Mutation class? All derived classes implement them. &lt;tt&gt;setTTL()&lt;/tt&gt; is in Mutation, and throws an exception when used with &lt;tt&gt;Delete&lt;/tt&gt;. So why not moved those down too? (cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=saint.ack%40gmail.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;saint.ack@gmail.com&quot;&gt;Stack&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
